p: Orbivirus sequences detected in Anopheles annulipes and An. hinesorum from Australia were named Anopheles annulipes orbivirus (AAOV) and Anopheles hinesorum orbivirus (AHOV) [ 31]. The viruses could not be cultured on C6/36 cells, but virus sequences were present in the mosquito 21-nucleotide viral RNA fraction, indicative of active replication and dicing of dsRNA replication intermediates.
